Great game

Love the game? Hardly. Hate it? Not quite, but definitely closer to it than loving it. Unresponsive controls, absolutely no momentum to movement, and "because I need it" logic for blocks. Most of the blocks will allow you to shoot thru them, some (read: all important ones) will not. Some roofs will let you jump all the way up to the floor above, some (completely arbitrary) will not and will cause you to hit the spikes.  It isn't hard because it's, well hard, but because it is unfair. It will all the time throw hidden enemies literally in your face and until you learn exactly where they are, you will take damage. Oh and don't get me started on the enemies on a small patrol pattern with a gun shooting from the wall to the left. The only place where shooting thru a block is needed, it is forbidden. I just wonder, if played for more than 7 levels, would there be some invisible one-shot enemies. I'm likely to say yes but it's just speculative.  Thankfully I managed to get the game for free but I will say, it's not worth the memory space it takes let alone it's price.
